transform property, along with its scale() function.
transform: scale(1.5);

The next function of the transform property is skewX(), which skews the selected element along its X (horizontal) axis 



::before creates a pseudo-element that is the first child of the selected element; ::after creates a pseudo-element that is the last child of the selected element
::before and ::after pseudo-elements are used to make shapes, the content property is still required, but it's set to an empty string.
